The paper discusses knowledge representation learning (KRL) which is a subfield of artificial intelligence (AI) that deals with representing entities and relations in knowledge graphs. Therefore, cs.AI is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses various machine learning techniques used in KRL, such as deep learning, which falls under the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses natural language processing (NLP) tasks such as language modeling, question answering, and information retrieval, which fall under the sub-category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also discusses knowledge graph completion and triple classification, which are related to database management (cs.DB). Finally, the paper discusses recommender systems, which fall under the sub-category of information retrieval (cs.IR).
